The paper discusses the design and implementation of a scalable member view management system for large-scale virtual clusters, which involves distributed systems, networking, operating systems, and system architecture. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also deals with network infrastructure and communication protocols, which falls under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Additionally, the paper discusses the implementation of a membership service, which is related to cs.OS (Operating Systems). The paper also presents a lightweight group membership algorithm, which is related to cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms). Finally, the paper deals with maintaining a consistent member view in virtual clusters, which is related to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
